---
/**
 * production-ai-architecture/0001 · Figure 3 (Module 1) — the graceful-degradation
 * ladder: step down (fallback → shorter context → cached/template → honest decline)
 * rather than hang.
 *
 * Verbatim copy of the source SVG (figure + svg + figcaption incl. footnote
 * <sup> #s2 / id="r2c"). References the shared #arw marker from Defs.astro.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A degradation ladder: as the primary model saturates, step down to a fallback model, then shorter context, then a cached or templated answer, then an honest decline, rather than hanging."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >When the model is slow / throttled / down — step down, don't hang</text
        >
        <rect x="20" y="40" width="118" height="44" rx="7" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="79" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Primary model</text
        >
        <text x="79" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f">full quality</text>
        <rect x="150" y="40" width="118" height="44" rx="7" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="209" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Fallback model</text
        >
        <text x="209" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >cheaper / faster</text
        >
        <rect x="280" y="40" width="118" height="44" rx="7" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="339" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Shorter context</text
        >
        <text x="339" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f">less work</text>
        <rect x="410" y="40" width="118" height="44" rx="7" fill="#f1eef2" stroke="#b5179e"></rect>
        <text x="469" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Cached / template</text
        >
        <text x="469" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f">no model call</text
        >
        <rect x="540" y="40" width="80" height="44" rx="7" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="580" y="58" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >Honest</text
        >
        <text x="580" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#9a2417">"can't now"</text>
        <line x1="138" y1="62" x2="148" y2="62" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="268" y1="62" x2="278" y2="62" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="398" y1="62" x2="408" y2="62" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="528" y1="62" x2="538" y2="62" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect x="20" y="118" width="600" height="56" rx="8" fill="#f6f4ef" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >The principle is older than AI: under saturation, drop quality to preserve
            availability.</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="158" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >A degraded answer beats a 30-second hang; an honest "I can't" beats a confident wrong
            answer.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The fallback model is the AI equivalent of a read replica or a static cached page — a
        cheaper, more-available path you route to when the primary is rate-limited, timing out, or
        down.<sup><a href="#s2" id="r2c">2</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
